        "title": "Chapter 1: The Anatomy of Rejection (5/23)",
        "content": "<p>He drops his hand.</p><p>The fluorescent tube buzzes.</p><p>Outside, through the louvered window, Manado is waking. Roosters. Motorcycles. Someone&#39;s radio playing a pop worship song about Jesus loving you exactly as you are.</p><p>Bobi does not believe this.</p><p>He knows the terms of the debt. He knows what the universe is owed.</p><p>He opens the door. The hallway waits. The bathroom waits. The mirror waits.</p><p>The payment plan is about to begin.</p><p>The hallway is narrow. Four doors, all closed except for the bathroom at the end, its door propped half-open with a plastic bucket. The walls are painted a color that might have been cream twenty years ago and is now the shade of teeth that have never seen a dentist. The floor tiles \u2014 once white, now grey \u2014 are cracked in a pattern that looks like a map of somewhere no one would want to visit.</p><p>Bobi walks the hallway barefoot. His feet know the path. Three steps, avoid the tile that shifts loose under weight, two more steps, shoulder past the narrow section where someone&#39;s motorbike mirror hangs on the wall for reasons he has never understood.</p><p>He reaches the bathroom.</p>"
