        "content": "<p>She said each name as she looked at each rectangle. &quot;Kyle.&quot; A smile. &quot;Julia.&quot; A nod. &quot;Klaudia.&quot; A warm acknowledgment. &quot;Mina\u2014I see you&#39;re camera-off, that&#39;s completely fine.&quot;</p><p>Then: &quot;Bobi.&quot;</p><p>His jaw locked again. The bone ground. His scalp flushed\u2014he felt the heat spreading across the naked skin, the pores opening, the sweat beginning.</p><p>She had said his name.</p><p>His name in her mouth, shaped by her accent, delivered in that voice that moved like fabric over a blade.</p><p>&quot;Hi,&quot; he said, unmuting quickly. The word came out higher than he intended. He muted again immediately.</p><p>Eline smiled. The expression transformed her face\u2014made the freckles shift slightly as her cheeks lifted, made her eyes narrow just enough to create small lines at the corners. She looked twenty-six. She looked like safety rendered in porcelain. She looked like the architectural blueprint of what beauty accepts.</p><p>Behind her, her apartment: a bookshelf with uniform spines, mostly cream and white. A succulent plant on a low table, its leaves thick and geometric. A lamp with a warm bulb\u2014the source of the golden light that had bloomed first. And on the wall, partially visible at the edge of the frame, a print. Bobi recognized the style before he recognized the image: Magritte. <em>The Son of Man</em>, maybe, or something similar\u2014the bowler hat, the apple, the obscured face.</p><p>He memorized the arrangement. The way the lamp sat at a forty-five-degree angle to the camera. The way the bookshelf created a vertical line that divided the frame. The way the succulent&#39;s shadow fell against the wall. This was the environment that had produced her. This was the architecture that surrounded beauty.</p><p>His finger moved to the screen.</p>"
