        "content": "<p>&quot;Thank you,&quot; he said. His voice came out steady. The laugh came out steady. Everything visible on camera remained steady while his hand shook in the darkness below the desk.</p><p>&quot;I think it&#39;s really cool that you have someone there with you,&quot; Klaudia said, not looking up from her phone. Her face was illuminated by two light sources\u2014the ring light facing her and the phone screen beneath her. &quot;Like, built-in roommate.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Yes. Very convenient.&quot;</p><p>Kyle&#39;s eyes moved across his screen, reading something. Probably the game stats from their last Colonist session. Probably work emails. His face showed the minimal engagement of someone present but not invested.</p><p>Julia picked up her phone. Her fingers moved across the screen\u2014quick, precise. The movement of typing rather than scrolling.</p><p>Across Warsaw, in the same room or perhaps just the same city, Klaudia&#39;s phone buzzed. She glanced down, read something, typed a response.</p><p>The exchange happened in Polish, but the meaning crossed borders:</p><p><em>Did you see the blood on his cheek?</em></p><p>A pause. Klaudia&#39;s eyes flicked from her phone to her screen, studying Bobi&#39;s rectangle.</p><p><em>What blood?</em></p>"
