        "chapter": 3,
        "isChapterStart": false,
        "title": "Chapter 3: The \"Identical\" Incision (22/22)",
        "content": "<p>He opened YouTube and typed &quot;rhinoplasty&quot; into the search bar. Videos of sterile operating theaters filled the screen, surgeons in scrubs and masks leaning over anesthetized patients. He clicked on one, watching as the surgeon made incisions, sculpted cartilage, and sutured skin with practiced ease. The sound was off, the room filled only with the hum of the laptop and the distant drumming of rain on the tin roof.</p><p>Bobi looked at his towel of tools, then back at the screen. The gap between the sterile precision of the operating theater and the crude reality of his desk was vast, but he did not see it. He saw only preparation, a man readying himself for a necessary task.</p><p>He paused the video on a cross-section diagram of a nose, the internal structures labeled with medical terms he did not fully understand. He studied the image, tracing the lines with his finger, memorizing the shapes and angles. Then he turned to the Brother, sitting silent and unblinking in the corner.</p><p>&quot;This is for you,&quot; he said, his voice barely above a whisper. &quot;For us.&quot;</p><p>He picked up the knife, testing its edge against his thumb once more. The red line reappeared, a thin ribbon of blood welling up from the shallow cut. He nodded, a small smile playing at the corners of his mouth. He was ready.</p><p>The room held its breath, the air thick with anticipation and the scent of moonshine. The fluorescent tube flickered, casting strobing shadows on the walls, the cracked mirror reflecting a fragmented image of a man poised on the precipice of transformation.</p><p>Bobi took a deep breath, the knife steady in his hand. The decision was made, the tools were laid out, the tutorial paused on the screen. There was no turning back now. He was calm, resolute, a man prepared to carve away the past and sculpt a future in his own image.</p><p>The Brother watched from the corner, his unblinking eyes reflecting the blue glow of the laptop screen. The room was silent save for the distant rain and the steady buzz of the fluorescent tube. Bobi stood on the brink, the knife in his hand a promise, a threat, a tool of rebirth.</p><p>He turned to the mirror, his eyes meeting the split reflection of his face. The cracked glass showed him a man divided, a man in transition. He was ready to bridge that divide, to become the man he was always meant to be. The knife glinted in the blue light, a sliver of silver against the dark backdrop of the room.</p><p>Bobi took one last look at the Brother, drawing strength from the silent figure in the corner. Then he turned to the mirror, the knife poised, the decision made. He was ready to begin.</p>"
