        "content": "<p>Bobi adjusted his grip on the knife. The handle was slick with his sweat, the blade catching the blue light from the screen. He pressed it harder against his skin, just enough to feel the resistance, the give of flesh before the cut. The song swelled in his chest, the words lost to time but the tune still there, still whole.</p><p>For now.</p><p>The rain intensified, a sudden downpour rattling the louvers, the sound like static, like the group call\u2019s audio when too many voices spoke at once. The fluorescent light flickered, once, twice, the buzz rising in pitch before steadying. His reflection wavered in the uneven glow, the knife a silver slash across his face.</p><p>He inhaled.</p><p>The song broke off mid-note.</p><p>He exhaled.</p><p>The knife stayed. The room waited. The Brother didn\u2019t move.</p><p>One more breath.</p><p>Then\u2014</p><p><em>(the cut comes next)</em></p>"
