        "chapter": 4,
        "isChapterStart": false,
        "title": "Chapter 4: Scalpel and Stone (5/11)",
        "content": "<p>He set the knife down again, flexing his cramping fingers. The blade was dulling, the edge nicked from hitting bone. He didn\u2019t mind. He\u2019d sharpen it later if he needed to. For now, he wiped it on the towel, the fabric dark with blood, and picked up the sewing needle. The fishing line was already threaded, the spool sitting beside the laptop, the transparent line catching the blue light like a spider\u2019s web.</p><p>His hands shook as he lifted the needle.</p><p>He didn\u2019t register it as fear. Fear was for things that could go wrong. This was going <em>right</em>. The shaking was just the body adjusting, the structure settling into its new shape. He steadied his grip, pressing the needle\u2019s point to the skin beside his nostril.</p><p>The first puncture was the hardest.</p><p>He pushed.</p><p>The skin resisted\u2014then gave with a sound like a wet finger snapping. <em>Pop.</em> The needle slid through, the fishing line following. He pulled it taut, the skin puckering around the entry point. Blood welled fresh, but he ignored it. He was sewing now. He was <em>closing</em>.</p><p>The Brother watched from the corner, silent as always.</p><p>Bobi didn\u2019t look at him.</p><p>He didn\u2019t need to.</p><p>He knew what the Brother would say.</p>"
