        "content": "<p>Bobi smiled.</p><p>His lips were cracked, the sutures from the nose surgery pulling slightly, the blood from his scalp drying on his forehead, his temples, his neck. He could feel the strands of hair against his skin, the adhesive tacky beneath his fingers, the fishing line taut where it had been pulled. He could feel the vibration of becoming. He could feel the debt being repaid.</p><p>He was almost there.</p><p>He was almost identical.</p><p>He turned back to the desk.</p><p>The tools were waiting.</p><p>The mirror was waiting.</p><p>He was ready for the next step.</p><p>The fluorescent light buzzed, casting its sickly yellow glow over the room as Bobi turned toward the cracked mirror. His breath came shallow, his fingers twitching at his sides. The mirror waited, its jagged fissure splitting the reflection into two uneven halves\u2014just like him and the Brother, just like before and after, just like debt and repayment.</p><p>He stepped closer.</p>"
