        "title": "Chapter 5: The Silk Harvest (14/16)",
        "content": "<p>And then he stopped.</p><p>His fingers hovered over the keyboard. He could save this. He could capture it. He could compare it to Eline\u2019s screenshot, measure the progress, see how much closer he was now. But he didn\u2019t. Not yet. This moment was his first. This reveal was for him and the Brother.</p><p>He turned back to the mirror.</p><p>The reflection was still there, still split, still uneven. But it was <em>better</em>. The hair changed everything. It balanced the face. It corrected the proportions. It made him look\u2014</p><p>Like the Brother.</p><p>Like the man he was supposed to be.</p><p>He reached up again, his fingers tracing the strands, feeling the adhesive ridges beneath, the points where the fishing line entered his skin. To him, it felt like hair. To him, it felt like silk. To him, it felt like completion.</p><p>He turned to the Brother.</p><p>The Brother sat in the corner, unchanged, unchanging. The hair above his forehead was thinner now, the strands Bobi had taken leaving uneven patches, the material beneath slightly exposed. But the Brother didn\u2019t need perfection. The Brother was already perfect. The Brother was the blueprint. The blueprint didn\u2019t need to be beautiful. The blueprint just needed to <em>be</em>.</p><p>\u201cNow <em>torang</em> are closer,\u201d Bobi said, his voice soft, intimate. The Manado word rolled off his tongue, warm and familiar. <em>Torang</em>. We. Us. The way you spoke to a twin. The way you spoke to a part of yourself.</p>"
