        "content": "<p>The game ended.</p><p><em>&quot;Good game, everyone,&quot;</em> Kyle said, leaning back in his chair, his face still perfect, still symmetrical, still <em>winning.</em></p><p>Bobi didn\u2019t answer. His hand was wrapped around the plastic shard, the edges digging into his palm, leaving red crescents in his skin. He didn\u2019t unmute. Not yet. He needed a moment. Needed to breathe. Needed to prepare.</p><p>The group\u2019s rectangles began disappearing one by one\u2014Klaudia first, her bright smile vanishing with a <em>&quot;Night, everyone!&quot;</em> Julia next, her camera cutting to black without a word. Mina\u2019s rectangle stayed dark, her voice a low <em>&quot;Goodnight&quot;</em> before she, too, was gone.</p><p>Eline lingered. Her rectangle was still there, still warm, still <em>looking</em> at him. <em>&quot;Bobi?&quot;</em> she said, her voice soft. <em>&quot;You sure you\u2019re okay?&quot;</em></p><p>His fingers tightened around the shard. The edges bit into his skin, the pain sharp and bright and <em>good.</em> <em>&quot;Yes,&quot;</em> he said, finally unmuting. His voice was distant, even to him. <em>&quot;Good game.&quot;</em></p><p>She smiled. <em>&quot;Okay. Sleep well.&quot;</em></p><p><em>&quot;Yes,&quot;</em> he said. <em>&quot;Sleep well.&quot;</em></p><p>Her rectangle vanished.</p><p>The screen went dark.</p>"
