        "content": "<p>The laptop screen cast a blue glow over Bobi\u2019s face, the flight search results scrolling as he leaned in, squinting at the prices. Manado to Jakarta. Jakarta to Amsterdam. Amsterdam to Brussels. Brussels to Ghent. The route was clear. The logic was flawless.</p><p>He had been becoming the Brother for months. The nose. The jaw. The hair. The skin. Each step had been necessary. Each cut had been progress. Now, there was only one thing left to do.</p><p>He needed to show her.</p><p>Not through a screen. Not through pixels that softened and lied. In person. Face to face. So she could see what he had built. So she could touch the Brother\u2019s jaw, the Brother\u2019s nose, the Brother\u2019s skin\u2014now his. So she could finally understand.</p><p>His finger traced the screen, scrolling past dates, times, layovers. He didn\u2019t need the cheapest flight. He needed the right one. The one that would get him there when she was free. The one that would let him stand in her apartment, in her warm light, and say, <em>Here. This is me. This is who I was always meant to be.</em></p><p>He clicked on a date. The price appeared. His savings were enough. Barely. But it was enough.</p><p>He reached for the backpack on the bed. It was old, the fabric worn thin at the seams, the zipper sticky. He unzipped it and began folding his clothes\u2014two shirts, a pair of trousers, undergarments. He placed them inside with careful precision, smoothing the wrinkles, aligning the edges. The normalcy of the act was almost comforting. A man packing a bag. A man preparing to travel. A man with a destination.</p><p>His fingers brushed against the fabric of his shirt. The texture was rough under his fingertips, the weave uneven. He paused. His own clothes felt wrong now. Too loose. Too plain. Too <em>his</em>.</p><p>He turned to the Brother.</p><p>The Brother sat in the corner, motionless. The laptop\u2019s glow caught the edge of his face, the synthetic hair, the smooth expanse of his jaw. Perfect. Unchanging. Waiting.</p>"
