        "content": "<p>The Brother was waiting.</p><p>And Bobi was ready.</p><p>The fluorescent tube buzzed overhead, its light casting a sickly yellow glow over the room. Bobi knelt before the Brother, his fingers resting on the synthetic thighs, feeling the unnatural give beneath the fabric. The Brother\u2019s face was smooth, unlined, perfect\u2014the jaw sharp, the cheekbones high, the skin flawless. The eyes were open, unblinking, staring at nothing and everything at once.</p><p>Bobi exhaled slowly.</p><p>This wasn\u2019t violence.</p><p>This was devotion.</p><p>He reached up, his hands trembling not with fear but with reverence. His fingers brushed the Brother\u2019s cheek, tracing the line of the jaw, the curve of the cheekbone, the flat expanse of the forehead. The skin\u2014if it was skin\u2014was cool, slightly tacky, yielding in a way that wasn\u2019t quite right. It didn\u2019t feel like flesh. It felt like something <em>built</em>. Like something <em>waiting</em>.</p><p>\u201cYou\u2019ve always been the handsome one,\u201d Bobi murmured. His voice was soft, almost a whisper. \u201cThe village loved you first. The aunts kissed you first. The girls looked at you first. I was always second. Always <em>si jelek</em>.\u201d</p><p>His fingers moved to the Brother\u2019s temple, pressing lightly. The material gave slightly, like latex left too long in the sun. He could feel the structure beneath\u2014something rigid, something geometric. Not bone. Not muscle. Something else.</p><p>Something <em>made</em>.</p>"
