        "content": "<p>Pause.</p><p>Buzz.</p><p>Rain.</p><p>&quot;Then I come to you.&quot;</p><p>The needle hovered above his eyelid, its silver eye catching the laptop\u2019s blue glow. Bobi\u2019s breath came slow, measured, as if preparing for a sacred rite. The fishing line dangled, frayed and thinning, the same spool that had stitched his nose, his scalp, his jaw\u2014each puncture a step toward this moment. The tools had history. The knife that carved his cartilage, the adhesive that bonded the Brother\u2019s hair, the needle that first pressed against his cheek in the bathroom mirror\u2014all of them had been here before, guiding him closer to completion.</p><p>His reflection stared back. The mask\u2019s edges curled slightly where sweat and blood had seeped beneath, but the pixel forgave. The webcam preview softened the ruin, blurring the stitches into shadows, the swelling into strong bone. Only the eyes remained his own\u2014dark, wide, still capable of closing. The Brother\u2019s eyes never did. They were open, always. Event horizons. No blinking. No looking away.</p><p>Bobi\u2019s fingers trembled\u2014not from fear, but from the weight of the final step. He turned to the camera, to the grid of faces frozen in horror. Klaudia\u2019s hands still clamped over her ears, her ring light casting sharp shadows on her tears. Julia\u2019s mouth moved in silent curses, her green-grey eyes narrowed like a blade. Kyle\u2019s rectangle showed him hunched over his phone, fingers flying across the screen, voice a compressed growl of commands. Mina\u2019s lips moved in prayer, her beads clicking a steady rhythm beneath the chaos. And Eline\u2014</p><p>Eline\u2019s face filled her rectangle. Freckles like a constellation. Pale blue-grey eyes locked onto his. Tears tracked her cheeks, but her voice cut through the digital soup, clear as a blade:</p><p><em>&quot;Bobi. Bobi. Bobi. Please stop.&quot;</em></p><p>He didn\u2019t hear <em>stop</em>.</p>"
